SIMPLE: intermixture
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intermixture
<hw>In`ter*mix"ture</hw> <pr>(?; 135)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A mass formed by mixture; a mass of ingredients mixed.</def>
<rj><au>Boyle.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Admixture; an additional ingredient.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In this height of impiety there wanted not an
<qex>intermixture</qex> of levity and folly.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intermobility</ent>⟦br⟧
